Class TextEditor

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.Container
        • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.composite.editor.AbstractSimpleValueEditor<String>
          • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.composite.editor.TextEditor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.i2rd.configuration.ConfigurableObject, PropertyChangeListener, Iterable<Component>, EventListener, LocaleContextSource, Component, ValueEditor<String>, Editable, ListCellRenderer, ParentComponent, TableCellRenderer, TreeCellRenderer

    public class TextEditor
extends AbstractSimpleValueEditor<String>
implements com.i2rd.configuration.ConfigurableObject
    Text editor. A text editor provides an HTML structure like 
     
 &lt;div class="prop">
   &lt;label for="thevalueid">My Label&lt;/label>
   &lt;input type="text" id="thevalueid" class="val" value="This is the value being edited">
 &lt;/div>
    OR 
     
 &lt;div class="prop">
   &lt;label for="thevalueid" class="tal">My Label&lt;/label>
   &lt;textarea id="thevalueid" class="val">This is the value being edited&lt;/textarea>
 &lt;/div>
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)

      • getUIValue

        public String getUIValue(org.apache.logging.log4j.Level logErrorLevel)
        Description copied from interface: ValueEditor
        Get the value currently in the UI. This is useful to peek at the value prior to calling ValueEditor.commitValue(). If you need to know whether there is a change or if the UI is in a valid state call ValueEditor.getModificationState() or ValueEditor.validateUIValue(Notifiable).
        Specified by:
        getUIValue in interface ValueEditor<String>
        Parameters:
        logErrorLevel - if an error occurs, the log level to log it at.
        Returns:
        the value in the UI. Will be null if the UI can represent a null state or the value is invalid.
